866. NCHS Data Brief. 2015 Dec;(229):1-8.

Mortality in the United States, 2014.

Murphy SL, Kochanek KD, Xu J, Arias E.

This report presents 2014 U.S. final mortality data on deaths and death rates by 
demographic and medical characteristics. These data provide information on 
mortality patterns among U.S. residents by such variables as sex, race and 
ethnicity, and cause of death. Information on mortality patterns is key to 
understanding changes in the health and well-being of the U.S. population. Life 
expectancy estimates, age-adjusted death rates by race and ethnicity and sex, 
the 10 leading causes of death, and the 10 leading causes of infant death were 
analyzed by comparing 2014 final data with 2013 final data.

All material appearing in this report is in the public domain and may be 
reproduced or copied without permission; citation as to source, however, is 
appreciated.

